formula: a(n) ~ (n-1)!/2 * (-1)^n / (1-exp(r))^n, where r = -1.4265092278500059... is the root of the equation exp(2/r) + 2*exp(1/r) - 2*exp((r^2+1)/r) = 1. - _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 31 2013
author: Patrick Demichel (patrick.demichel(AT)hp.com)
extensions: Prepended missing a(0)=0, a(1)=0, _Vaclav Kotesovec_, Oct 31 2013
